We used the pool and steam room which was very clean.	We both used the gym, swimming pool and steam room (all complimentary) during our stay.	We used the pool and sauna - nice options after a day of touring.	We also used the amenities (indoor pool) and my wife and her sister used the spa services.	The pool is calm and peaceful and very welcome after a busy sight seeing day.	The pool, although below ground level and small, is still lovely.	The pool and locker room were also clean and bright but if you book a massage you must pay in cash.	Unfortunately they were renovating the spa area so we could not try out the swimming pool.